content: Thunderstorms have always helped me sleep and this app has awesome ones. Plus, you can adjust so many things like the type of rain, frequency of thunder, etc. I definitely recommend.

No lightning happening on my Galaxy S7. Just the sound effects. Update: After giving it permission to access the camera it worked. I left it on default for 30 minutes and it drained my battery overnight though. Timer was set for 30 minutes - I fell asleep - so not sure what that is about. Will continue testing.
replyContent: Hi Mike, please make sure the app has permission to access your camera: Settings - Apps - Thunderstorm Simulator - Permissions - Toggle on Camera. Contact support@thunderstorm.scottdodson.dev for help. Thank you.

content: Works great on my galaxy a5 , Oreo. Nice work , good deal .

This App is so generic it should be free. That's why they dont let you try 
it. There are much better free apps out there, that sound better, and do so 
much more. I know it was only $1 but its $1 totally wasted!!! Do not buy, 
it's not worth it.
replyContent: Sorry to hear you don't enjoy the app. Thunderstorm Simulator provides a premium experience with no ads. Please see Settings for more options. If there is a feature you think is missing, please email support@thunderstorm.scottdodson.io with your feedback. I can also give you a refund.

content: Thank you for this app, it's everything I have been looking for.
Everything I can think of that I want in thunderstorm sounds app. I really appreciate the different delays between near and far lightning, and the fade out at the end of the timer.
Bought Thunderstorm for Hue for the home then Thunderstorm Simulator to take with me... both great products. Very relaxing!
If you enjoy falling asleep to the sound of rain, this is your app. It's pretty cool that the flash goes off to simulate lightning. Also, I love the new add ons; cicadas, birds, tin roof, etc!
I've been looking for an app like this for years. I'm super happy. Sound is great, camera light flashes with lightning/thunder.  Love it!
Looks awesome with the lights off, almost like the real thing. Sleep timer is a great addition as well.
